<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-5260] LDAP Component lose headers</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-5260</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When we call to a LDAP endpoint, the result is returned in the Out body and we lose the IN headers (see &lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/LDAP-Component-lose-headers-td5696602.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/LDAP-Component-lose-headers-td5696602.html&lt;/a&gt;). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A fix seems relatively easy. The solution could be add this line inside the process() method in LdapProducer.java&lt;br/&gt;
 exchange.getOut().setHeaders(exchange.getIn().getHeaders());&lt;/p&gt;</description>
